For me it was a combination of the following:

* Anger and feeling singled out for toxicity in a game where toxic behavior is absolutely rampant (especially @ low bronze ranked)
{{sticker:zombie-brand-mindblown}} 
* Elation at the apparent ease of just leveling another fresh account from 0-30 with ranked unlocked in just over 3 weeks.  Presto! Clean record.
{{sticker:slayer-pantheon-thumbs}} 
* Vengeful and calculating now knowing that the IFS can be weaponized against other players.  Now I report practically everyone I encounter that rubs me even slightly wrong.
{{sticker:slayer-jinx-wink}} 
* Smug in the knowledge that I am unafraid of occasional IFS penalties with this method of getting around them.
{{sticker:slayer-pantheon-popcorn}}

You're the type of person I repeatedly gank 

{{sticker:darius-angry}} 

But yeah that's smart lol and tbh the knowledge of just how easy it is to get punished works well in keeping yourself from tilting. Why get tilted when you know damn well you can report someone and have them banned for saying "report them for feeding"
